What makes me a great fit for your team

  • Fun and Charismatic

    Your office will be filled with laughter, whether it's at my jokes or at my code. Either way, team morale is guaranteed to skyrocket (or at least hit terminal velocity).

  • If It Ain't Broke, I'll Break It

    A well-functioning codebase is a great start—but can it be better? I'll refactor, debug, and push it to its limits until it's unrecognizable… in a good way. Trust me, it’ll work better when I’m done (eventually).

  • Readable Code > Good Looks

    Some developers write code. I write bedtime stories for compilers. Clear, structured, and so easy to read, even your grandma will understand what a dependency injection is (probably).

  • Test-Driven Development... Kinda

    I write tests. Not always first, but definitely after something breaks. If debugging is the process of removing bugs, then I am a prolific bug producer, ensuring my code is thoroughly battle-tested.

  • Stack Overflow Enthusiast

    I may not know everything, but I sure know where to find it! From Stack Overflow to documentation deep dives, I wield the power of Ctrl+C and Ctrl+V with precision, backed by actual understanding (most of the time).
